About Me

My journey into data and product analysis began during my academic years and deepened through professional roles. At Infosys, I served as a Software Engineer where I analyzed real‑time financial transaction data to identify fraud patterns and reduced false positives by 30% through refined detection logic and optimized thresholds. I collaborated closely with analysts, QA engineers and stakeholders in an Agile setting, developing dashboards and reports that facilitated informed decision‑making.

Previously, as a Project Intern at Atom Software Solutions, I designed an IoT‑based home automation system, integrating sensor data and utilizing MQTT for real‑time communication. This role taught me the importance of aligning technology solutions with user needs and iterating based on data insights.

Key Projects

University Recommendation System

Developed a web application that recommends universities based on user academic and personal profiles. Implemented backend logic using Flask and machine learning models such as K‑Nearest Neighbors (KNN), Decision Trees and Random Forests. Integrated AJAX for real-time interactions and created a responsive front end. The system achieved high prediction accuracy and received positive usability feedback.

Vulnerability Scanning & Remediation Process

Led a team to scan and remediate security vulnerabilities on a Metasploitable virtual machine. Analyzed scan results to prioritize remediation, documented findings and corrective actions and produced comprehensive reports. The project improved system security and ensured stakeholders understood risks and fixes.

Music Genre Classification

Built a classifier to identify music genres using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Preprocessed audio data with Mel‑Frequency Cepstral Coefficients (MFCCs) to extract features and established a robust data pipeline for training and evaluation. Achieved high classification accuracy, demonstrating the capability to apply deep learning techniques to signal processing problems.
